 149:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *
 150:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  This function allows the caller to read data from the bootloader host. It 
 151:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  handles polling to allow a block of data to be completely received from the 
 152:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  host device.
 153:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *
 154:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  \param pData    A pointer to the area to store the block of data received
 155:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *                  from the device.
 156:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  \param size     The number of bytes to read.
 157:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  \param count    Pointer to an unsigned short variable to write the number
 158:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *                  of bytes actually read.
 159:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  \param timeOut  Number of units to wait before returning because of a timeOut.
 160:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *                  Timeout is measured in 10s of ms.
 161:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *
 162:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** * \return
 163:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  Returns CYRET_SUCCESS if no problem was encountered or returns the value that 
 164:Generated_Source\PSoC4/USBFS_boot.c **** *  best describes the problem. For more information, see the “Return Codes” 
